gw.api.diff.traverser

Class PairedGraphTraverser

  • java.lang.Object
    • gw.api.diff.traverser.PairedGraphTraverser

  • public abstract class PairedGraphTraverser
extends java.lang.Object
    Perform a recursive (deep) diff on two beans, with a public interface for controlling each step, and a matching interface for comparing array members.
    Author:
    dmccreary

      • pairArray

        protected java.util.List<Pair<KeyableBean,KeyableBean>> pairArray(KeyableBean[] ones,
                                                                  KeyableBean[] twos,
                                                                  KeyableBean oneParent,
                                                                  KeyableBean twoParent,
                                                                  IArrayPropertyInfo arrayProperty)
        When an array is to be visited, its members must be paired up for visitation, and this method allows the sub-classer to override that pairing. The default implementation simply pairs them in the order received. Excess items are paired with a null.
        Parameters:
        ones - the first array's contents
        twos - the second array's contents
        oneParent - the parent of the first array
        twoParent - the parent of the second array
        arrayProperty - the property representing the array
        Returns:
        pairing of all of the array elements to be traversed pairwise
